name: Middlemead
description: Tumbling down through the crags and gullies of The North Rim, freshwater rivulets become streams, streams become rivers and all those flow tward Cadwell and the sea.  Avoiding a band of fourteen sullen men and with the help of their tracker, the company travelled off the road in wooded valleys and dappled glades. A further four days picking their way along these rivers through woods of alder and white willow brought them within sight Middlemead.
